New Records: Stephen Curry scored a season-high 36 points
Key Match Events: Stephen Curry hit two clutch 3-pointers, including one with his signature 'night night' celebration
Jonathan Kuminga scored 12 points in the second quarter to help the Warriors turn a seven-point deficit into a seven-point lead
Stephen Curry scored 17 points in the third quarter, nearly outscoring the Thunder by himself in the frame
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors finished the difficult road trip with a 4-1 record
The Warriors will return to Chase Center for the Emirates NBA Cup, beginning against Klay Thompson, Luka Doncic, Kyrie Irving and the Dallas Mavericks on Tuesday
Others: Draymond Green dished out a game-high 11 assists, generating 25 points for the Warriors
De'Anthony Melton had his highest scoring output as a Warrior, finishing with 19 points
The Thunder lost 7-footer Chet Holmgren to injury early in the first quarter
